ates in the west, the minting and currency of the Visigoths reveal shared patterns as well as originality. The analysis brings both economic life and the needs of the state into sharper focus, with significant implications for the study of an essential element in daily life and government. This study combines an appreciation for the surprising level of sophistication in the Visigothic minting system with an accessible approach to a subject which can seem complex and abstruse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aMoneyzSpainxHistory. 0aVisigothszSpain. 4aAntiquity. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aEconomics and Finance. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMedieval Studies. 4aPolitics and Government. 7aANTIQUES & COLLECTIBLES / Coins, Currency & Medals.2bisacsh  aEarly Medieval Economy.  aIslamic Conquest in Iberia.  aVisigothic Currency.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048531301zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048531301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048531301/original  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amster